#### Comparable engines

For those who enjoy comparing apples to slightly different, yet functionally similar, apples, here are a few other radial engines from the same general period and power class that often found themselves in similar applications:

*   [Bristol Jupiter](/Bristol_Jupiter): A prominent British nine-cylinder radial, known for its widespread use in the interwar period, often seen as a benchmark for early radial design.
*   [Continental R-670](/Continental_R-670): Another American seven-cylinder radial that competed directly with the R-680 in the trainer and utility aircraft markets, offering similar power ranges.
*   [Jacobs R-755](/Jacobs_R-755): A seven-cylinder American radial engine, slightly larger in displacement, often found in smaller transport and agricultural aircraft.
*   [Pratt & Whitney R-985](/Pratt_%26_Whitney_R-985): A larger, more powerful nine-cylinder radial, part of Pratt & Whitney's renowned Wasp Junior series, often used in larger trainers and light transport aircraft, setting a higher bar for performance.
*   [Wright R-790 Whirlwind](/Wright_R-790_Whirlwind): An early American nine-cylinder radial from a key competitor, part of the extensive Whirlwind family that powered many significant aircraft of the 1920s and 30s.

